Q.  D/f b/w Package.json OR Package.lock.json ?
A.  package.json - 
    🔹Stores the direct dependencies and project configuration required for the application.
    "react": "^18.2.0"
    🔹Uses version ranges (^, ~) so npm can install compatible newer versions.

    package-lock.json
    🔹Stores the exact installed version of every package, including all sub-dependencies (nested dependencies).
    "react": {
      "version": "18.2.0"
    }
    🔹Ensures same dependency installation for every developer/system by locking the complete dependency tree.




Q.  What is node_modules?
A.  node_modules -
    node_modules is the folder that stores all installed npm packages, including direct and transitive (sub) dependencies.
    When we run:
    npm install axios:
    npm installs axios and its required sub-packages, then stores all those package files inside node_modules.
